Functional Requirements: Functional Requirement defines a function of a software system and
how the system must behave when presented with specific inputs or conditions. These may include
calculations, data manipulation and processing and other specific functionality. In this system following
are the functional requirements

Training dataset must be loaded
User enters the URL in URL locator.
URL must be detected and display whether it is legitimate or non-fake website.
Other Non-Functional Requirements
A non-functional requirement is a determination that depicts the framework’s activity abilities and
requirements that improve its usefulness.
Some of them are as follows:
Reusability: the same code with limited changes can be used for detecting phishing attacks variants
like smishing, vishing, etc.
Maintainability: The implementation is very basic and includes print statements that makes it easy
to debug.
Usability: The software used is very user friendly and open source. It also runs on any
operating system.
Scalability: The implementation can include detection of vishing, smishing, etc.
Maintainability: It maintains clean code, easily upgradable, automated testing.
Reliability: The system is reliable by controlling accuracy, uptime and resilience.
